<paragraph blockId="34.[192,1440,1731,1915]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,744,1731,1755]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Identification, taxonomy, and variation.</emphasis>
Both sexes bear a light reddish buff ground color, similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[221,525,1763,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="chitone">
<emphasis box="[221,525,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Speyeria hesperis chitone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Their appearance overall is pale, and lacks the red hues of other 
<taxonomicName box="[1310,1439,1763,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hesperis">
<emphasis box="[1310,1328,1764,1787]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1340,1439,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">hesperis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[244,370,1795,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantis">
<emphasis box="[244,262,1796,1819]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[275,370,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">atlantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms. Adult wingspan ranges from 
<quantity box="[811,936,1795,1819]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="47.5" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="45.0">45-50 mm</quantity>
. Authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Hodges, R. W." box="[1115,1274,1795,1819]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" refId="ref40560" refString="Hodges, R. W. 1983. Check list of the Lepidoptera of American North of Mexico. E. W. Classey Limited; Oxfordshire, England. 284 p." type="book" year="1983">Hodges 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Austin, G. T." box="[1284,1435,1795,1819]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" pagination="629 - 640" refId="ref33956" refString="Austin, G. T. 1998. Type data for butterflies described from Nevada. p. 629 - 640. In: T. C. Emmel (ed.). Systematics of western North American butterflies. Mariposa Press; Gainesville, Florida. 878 p." type="book chapter" year="1998">Austin 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Scott, J. A. &amp; N. G. Kondla &amp; S. M. Spomer" box="[192,381,1827,1851]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref45136" refString="Scott, J. A., N. G. Kondla, and S. M. Spomer. 1998. Speyeria hesperis and Speyeria atlantis are distinct species. Papilio 8: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1998">Scott et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
) inadvertently included parentheses around the describer Moeck, suggesting this species was originally described in another genus. This has been perpetuated in the literature; however, ‘ 
<emphasis box="[1374,1434,1860,1883]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">greyi</emphasis>
’ was originally described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1872" box="[524,630,1892,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[524,630,1892,1915]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Speyeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the parentheses were in error (
<bibRefCitation author="Dunford, J. C. &amp; G. T. Austin" box="[1059,1372,1891,1915]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref36235" refString="Dunford, J. C., and G. T. Austin. 2007. Nomenclatural faux pas for Speyeria atlantis greyi Moeck, 1950 (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae). Insecta Mundi 0017: 1 - 4." type="book chapter" year="2007">Dunford and Austin 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[192,1307,195,220]" box="[192,1307,195,220]" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">
